    "For evaluating the topic similarity of two vertices, we use the cosine function:Sim(u, v) = cos(u, v) = u⋅v |u| * |v|.",
    "Graph Reconstruction AlgorithmSearching for communities through meta-structures is a challenging task, since vertices have many neighbors, and various combinations will appear when the metastructure has lots of bifurcations.",
    "For one vertex, if the meta-structure has m branches, then there would be ∏ m i n i combinations, where n i is the number of neighbors of that vertex of the ith type.",
    "In large networks where each vertex has numerous neighbors, combining neighbors in the searching process results in a high time complexity.",
    "Fortunately, the searching meta-structures are typically static, while query vertices and constraints may change."
